Peaches Browning https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peaches_Browning 0 Peaches Browning (June 23, 1910 – August 23, 1956), born Frances Belle Heenan, was an American actress. She was married to New York City real estate developer Edward West "Daddy" Browning (1875–1934). Their story became one of the most sensational "scandals" of the Roaring Twenties. It is often cited in journalism history texts as an example of the excesses of tabloid newspapers during the era.
